
[1]complot

   COMPLOT, n. A plotting together; a joint plot; a plot; a confederacy in
   some evil design; a conspiracy.

   I know their complot is to have my life.

   COMPLOT, v.t. To plot together; to conspire; to form a plot; to join in
                    a secret design, generally criminal.

   We find them complotting together, and contriving a new scene of
   miseries to the Trojans.
